# ── Rust / Cargo build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Cargo writes all build output to `target/`. This must never be committed.
# The repo has Cargo workspaces under src/edge-ingress and src/envoy, so
# we ignore both top-level and nested target/ directories.
target/
**/target/
# Per-workspace Cargo state.
**/.cargo-lock
.cargo/
# Cargo intermediate library outputs (defensive; usually inside target/).
*.rlib
*.rmeta
# Debug symbols emitted by some Rust toolchains.
*.pdb
*.dSYM/
# WASM artifacts produced by `cargo build --target wasm32-wasi`. The
# deployable .wasm is published by CI (helm `--set-file wasm.base64=...`),
# not committed to source control.
*.wasm
# NOTE: Cargo.lock is intentionally NOT ignored. We commit it for binary
# crates (edge-ingress) per the official Cargo guidance to make builds
# reproducible. Library-only crates that are published to crates.io would
# typically ignore Cargo.lock, but no crate in this repo is published.
